  "feedback": "## ATX Review — Issue #795 Iter 2\n\n**Rating: 4/5 | No blockers | 1 warning + 8 suggestions**\n\nAll three specialists confirmed the core implementation is correct. No blocking issues. One consistent warning across two specialists requires attention before merge.\n\n---\n\n### Implementation Verification (lifecycle-core)\n\nAll six verification questions from the task resolved **pass**:\n\n| Q | Result |\n|---|--------|\n| Q1 — assert form | Correct. `not frozenset()` is truthy when sets are disjoint; fires when they overlap |\n| Q2 — mutation safety | Safe. `json.load` produces fresh dict trees; nothing else holds references; no escape path |\n| Q3 — guard ordering | Correct. `isinstance(agents, dict)` → `isinstance(record, dict)` → `isinstance(config, dict)` in right order |\n| Q4 — Group B preservation | Enforced positively. Loop only iterates `_PRUNED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS`; Group B keys are never named |\n| Q5 — pipeline order | Correct and order-independent. `_apply_legacy_defaults` only backfills `os_family`; pruning as outermost wrapper produces identical result |\n| Q6 — pruned set completeness | Complete. Grep confirms no writes to `config[\"integrations\"]`, `config[\"memory\"]`, `config[\"skills\"]` anywhere in `src/clawrium` |\n\n---\n\n### Warning\n\n**W1 — `assert` disabled under `python -O` / `PYTHONOPTIMIZE`** *(security-reviewer + lifecycle-core)*\n`src/clawrium/core/hosts.py:289`\n\nThe comment explicitly states this guard exists to prevent a future maintainer from widening `_PRUNED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS` into Group B, which would silently wipe `config.gateway.auth` on every load. An `assert` is stripped when Python runs under `-O` or `PYTHONOPTIMIZE=1` (common in some container images), defeating the stated purpose.\n\n**Fix:**\n```python\n# Replace:\nassert not (_PRUNED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS \u0026 _PRESERVED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS), (\n    \"Group B keys must never appear in _PRUNED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS\"\n)\n\n# With:\nif _PRUNED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS \u0026 _PRESERVED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS:\n    raise RuntimeError(\n        \"Group B keys must never appear in _PRUNED_AGENT_CONFIG_KEYS\"\n    )\n```\nSame cost, survives optimization.\n\n---\n\n### Suggestions\n\n**S1 — `cli/status.py` silent display regression** *(security-reviewer)*\n`cli/status.py:175-178` reads `claw_record.get('config', {}).get('provider', {}).get('type')` for the fleet-status display column. After pruning, this always returns `None` → renders `-`. Not a security issue, but the provider column silently goes blank for all pre-#794 agents on first load. Either migrate to reading from canonical `providers.json` in this PR, or document the display change in CHANGELOG and open a follow-up.\n\n**S2 — Stale credential eviction is lazy, not eager** *(security-reviewer)*\n`config.channels.discord.bot_token` (a real Discord credential) is stripped from the in-memory view on load but remains on-disk until a write path fires. The CHANGELOG should note that operators wanting immediate eviction of stale credentials should run any lifecycle op (e.g. `clawctl agent configure`) to force a `save_hosts` round-trip.\n\n**S3 — Migration runs forever with no removal anchor** *(lifecycle-core)*\n`src/clawrium/core/hosts.py:294-316`\n\nAdd a TODO comment:\n```python\n# TODO(post-v27): remove once all hosts.json files have round-tripped post-#794\n```\n\n**S4 — Missing `config: {}` test case** *(test-coverage)*\n`test_load_hosts_handles_non_dict_config` covers `None/str/int/list` (non-dict) but not `{}` (empty dict). Empty dict hits the `isinstance(config, dict)` True branch with nothing to strip and should round-trip as `{}`. Separate from the non-dict parametrize since it is a dict:\n```python\ndef test_load_hosts_handles_empty_config(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    ...\n    hosts = load_hosts()\n    assert hosts[0][\"agents\"][\"demo\"][\"config\"] == {}\n```\n\n**S5 — Missing `agents: None` host edge case** *(test-coverage)*\n`test_load_hosts_handles_host_without_agents` covers the missing-key case but not `\"agents\": None`. The `isinstance(agents, dict)` guard handles it correctly but there's no test that locks it down. Also worth adding `\"agents\": {}` (empty dict — trivially safe but cheap).\n\n**S6 — Idempotence test doesn't prove the first save actually pruned** *(test-coverage)*\n`test_load_save_round_trip_is_idempotent` compares `first_bytes == second_bytes` — proving iter-2 → iter-3 stability — but a bug where `save_hosts` re-introduces the pruned keys would still pass. Add:\n```python\noriginal_bytes = (config_dir / HOSTS_FILE).read_bytes()\nsave_hosts(load_hosts())\nfirst_bytes = (config_dir / HOSTS_FILE).read_bytes()\nassert b'\"provider\"' not in first_bytes\nassert len(first_bytes) \u003c len(original_bytes)\n```\n\n**S7 — Strip test doesn't assert exact key set** *(test-coverage)*\n`test_load_hosts_strips_group_a_key` asserts `stripped_key not in config` and `config[preserved_key] == preserved_value` but not that no stray keys were introduced. Add:\n```python\nassert set(config.keys()) == {preserved_key}\n```\n\n**S8 — `_patch_config_dir`'s `init_config_dir` lambda doesn't mkdir** *(test-coverage)*\nThe lambda `lambda: config_dir` doesn't create the directory. Tests pass today only because `_write_hosts` creates it first. Future tests calling `save_hosts` without a prior `_write_hosts` would fail confusingly. Make the lambda create the dir to match production semantics.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| # | Type | Location | Status |\n|---|------|----------|--------|\n| W1 | `assert` → `if/raise RuntimeError` | `hosts.py:289` | **Address before merge** |\n| S1 | `cli/status.py` display regression | `cli/status.py:176` | Follow-up or CHANGELOG note |\n| S2 | Stale credential lazy eviction | CHANGELOG | Note in CHANGELOG |\n| S3 | Migration removal TODO | `hosts.py:294` | One-line comment |\n| S4 | `config: {}` test | `test_hosts.py` | New test |\n| S5 | `agents: None`/`{}` test | `test_hosts.py` | New tests |\n| S6 | Idempotence test pre-save bytes | `test_hosts.py:159-184` | Strengthen assertion |\n| S7 | Exact key-set assertion | `test_hosts.py:103-104` | Add `set(config.keys())` check |\n| S8 | `init_config_dir` lambda | `test_hosts.py:21-26` | Add `mkdir` |\n\nW1 is the only item requiring a code change in `hosts.py` before merge. Suggestions S3-S8 are test/comment improvements; S1-S2 can be addressed in follow-ups with CHANGELOG documentation.\n",
